*** ChanServ Help - Command: RESETPASS ***
Resets the password of a registered channel.

This command is used together with SENDPASS. A helper or
services operator starts the password reset with SENDPASS
#channel: an authorization code is then sent by E-Mail to the
address registered for the channel founder, along with further
instructions.

Once you receive the reset code by E-Mail, identify to your
founder nick (/ns IDENTIFY) and use RESETPASS to set a new
channel password. The new password must be at least 5
characters long, must not contain spaces or control codes,
and must not be the same as the channel name.

The reset code is valid for 7 days. After that the request
expires and a fresh SENDPASS is needed.

You do NOT need to be identified to the channel to run this
command: being able to receive E-Mail at the address tied to
the founder nickname is the proof of ownership.

To cancel a pending password reset request, contact a
services operator to run AUTHRESET on the channel.

Syntax:

/cs RESETPASS #channel code new-password

Example:
/cs RESETPASS #lamer 1234567 n3wP4ssw0rd

Type /join #IRCHelp for more information.
*** End of Help ***
